Armed robbers have attacked four banks in the Uromi area of Edo State, leaving many bank customers injured while the number of deaths has yet to be ascertained. SaharaReporters learnt that the robbers on Thursday attacked Zenith, First Bank, UBA and Union Bank in the area, leading to confusion among residents and bank customers in the area. 





According to a video sent to SaharaReporters, gunshots boomed in the area as residents and passersby scampered to safety. It is not clear yet the extent of damage done by the armed robbers to the banks.